<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-07-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-07-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="137" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                        <head>No. 133.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Flores</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington, D. C.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-07-04"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 4, 1885</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I am most happy to announce you that, according to official cablegram
                            just received, the amnesty has been granted.</p>
                        <closer><signed>ANTONIO FLORES.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>